{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PLAN-REVIEW REMEDIATION (Round-11, 2026-06-29) — disposition of the 20 advisory (+5 overflow, 3 dropped) findings. Derisk experiment evidence in session_log a7e2-381c-6dc6-4d0c (EXPERIMENT 1).\n\nRESOLVED — gitleaks/semgrep fit (T1+T3 critical): PROVEN — semgrep is the opengrep YAML-rule format and passes metadata.rebar_envelope through verbatim + emits SARIF 2.1.0 → ships as detector YAML on the existing opengrep backend (no new backend); gitleaks uses TOML + compiled-in rules (NOT a detector YAML) but emits SARIF 2.1.0 → integrated via a generic SARIF-ingest backend (serves semgrep too). Pinned on epic + WS5 (bba6).\nRESOLVED — fail-OPEN vs fail-CLOSED conflict (T3 critical): PROVEN Engine B is fail-open by invariant; fail-closed now lives in THIS gate's Pass-3 consumer (abstain on secrets/sec detector → BLOCK + coverage-gap), not the oracle. WS5 AC.\nRESOLVED — semgrep ruleset unspecified + diff vs repo scope (E2/T3 major): named vendored subset (p/owasp-top-ten + p/cwe-top-25), diff-scoped. WS5.\nRESOLVED — WS2↔WS5 threshold-resolver ownership (G4 major): WS2 owns threshold_for + ships the two security criterion keys as blocking_enabled=False placeholders; WS5 flips them True. Explicit on both.\nRESOLVED — base-reviewer failure fallback (T8 major): empty findings + glob-only Round-B + coverage-gap; never auto-BLOCK (recall-side). WS1.\nRESOLVED — recommend_overlays output schema fields (T8 major): {overlay_id enum, reason required ≤200 chars}; dual named outputs. WS1.\nRESOLVED — overlay_union already-run input wiring (T8 major): explicit with: input from the Round-A triggers output. WS3.\nRESOLVED — merge_findings dedup/clustering (G6 major): clusters by file-anchor+dimension+line-proximity before Pass-2. WS3.\nRESOLVED — escalation-mechanism ADR (T7/T5e major): ADR for the one-hop base→overlay design. WS3.\nRESOLVED — gates/code-review.yaml schema doc (T7 major): documented schema AC. WS3.\nRESOLVED — back-out shim return value + one-way-door contradiction (T4 + COH/E1 major): disabled → review_code() returns valid empty review_result (+ disabled note), never error/stub; reverting the flag yields INERT, NOT restored single-pass — stated honestly; ADR records the one-way door. WS4 + epic.\nRESOLVED — Gerrit voter staged rollout (T12 critical): per-project/staged opt-in before fleet-wide. WS6 + epic.\nRESOLVED — fail-closed BLOCK surfacing in Gerrit vote (G4 minor): coverage-gap -1 surfaced distinctly from a real-finding -1. WS6.\nRESOLVED — stale code_review.py references (T7 minor): WS4 audits docs/CLI-help.\nRESOLVED — diff-assembler import survives WS4 retirement (G4 major): assemble.py has no code_review.py import; test pins it. WS1.\nNOTED — G5 (first e2e vertical slice only at WS4): kept. The epic already documents WS1-WS5 are fully testable via the rebar review-code CLI/MCP without Gerrit, and WS6 is de-riskable against a STUB Gerrit; a thinner slice would re-cut the WS boundaries for marginal gain. Justified, not silently ignored.\nNOTED — P6 (DoD quality on child ACs): addressed by the per-child AC additions above."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782766449040797001,"uuid":"2dd2a88a-808d-417d-8447-5c25c13081bd"}